\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\fnorm{a+\rmi b}=a^{2}+b^{2}\,.\label{fieldnorm.eq}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

We avoid the square root in the discrete field framework because, unlike
 the continuous case, the square root does not always exist.
\end_layout

