 Then, starting with 
\begin_inset Formula $n=3$
\end_inset

, we can pick fully entangled 2-qubit subspaces as product spaces, combining
 them with single-qubit product components (
\begin_inset Formula $n=3$
\end_inset

 has no single-qubit freedom left after picking any of its three 2-qubit
 subspaces), and so on.
